%N A392283 Numbers k such that phi(k) divides k + 3.
%C A392283 All terms after a(2) are odd due to parity reasons.
%C A392283 Conjecture: terms in this sequence after 9 are identical to A039777.
%C A392283 Contains 3*t for terms t of A203966 that are coprime to 3 and have even quotient (t+1)/phi(t). - _Max Alekseyev_, Mar 06 2026
%C A392283 No other terms below 10^26. Some large terms: 1039619980803100740810795122685, 32576974833437288924302842789885. - _Max Alekseyev_, Mar 09 2026
%e A392283 21 is a term because phi(21) = 12, which divides 21+3 = 24.
%t A392283 fQ[n_] := Mod[n + 3, EulerPhi[n]] == 0; k=3; lst = {1, 2}; While[k < 10^12, If[ Mod[k +3, EulerPhi[ k]] == 0, AppendTo[lst, k]]; k += 2]; lst (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Feb 01 2026 *)
%o A392283 (Python)
%o A392283 from sympy import totient
%o A392283 def ok(n): return n > 0 and (n+3) % totient(n) == 0
%o A392283 print([k for k in range(200000) if ok(k)])
